Primarily changing the following for RX/TX
1. Frequency
2. Bandwidth
3. Sampling Rate
4. Gain Mode / Value
5. Enables I and Q channels (storing phase in both real/imaginary domain)
Values can be changed in JSON file

On raspberry pi install following:
sudo apt install libiio-utils libiio-dev 
pip install pylibiio
pip install numpy

Can use IIO oscilloscope software to validiate parameters besides test script

Reference: https://analogdevicesinc.github.io/libiio/v0.25/python/index.html

# launching venv on Pi
source /home/abraho2/Desktop/roverenv/SDR/venv/bin/activate

# GNU radio installation
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

sudo apt install -y gnuradio

sudo apt install -y git cmake g++ libboost-all-dev python3-pip
sudo apt install -y swig liborc-0.4-dev

gnuradio-config-info --version

# install gr-lora
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/rpp0/gr-lora.git
cd gr-lora

mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make -j4  # Use all 4 cores on Pi
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig

python3 -c "import lora; print('gr-lora installed successfully!')"

# pluto SDR config
sudo apt install -y libiio-utils libiio-dev
sudo apt install -y gr-iio
iio_info -u ip:192.168.2.1